Balletpedia https://ballotpedia.org/Attorney_General_of_Hawaii lists the AG duties as:

1. Representing the state in civil and criminal cases in which it is a party;
2. Investigating violations of state laws;
3. Preparing official legal opinions for the governor, the state legislature, and other state agencies;
4. Advising state officials on legal matters;
5. Defending state employees in matters related to their official duties.

That sounds like what Chin has been doing the last year.
